{"key":"post-9666505","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9666505</id>\n<content>If it draws 13.25 amps, you can't &lt;i&gt;legally&lt;/i&gt; run it on a 15 amp circuit.&amp;nbsp; Any appliance that runs for more than an hour is considered a continuous load, and the circuit must be de-rated to 80%, according to the National Electrical Code, which sets &lt;i&gt;minimum standards&lt;/i&gt; to avoid fire.&amp;nbsp; Thus, you could only 'safely' operate it on a 20 amp circuit.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9666621</next>\n<prev>9666241</prev>\n<first>9647794</first>\n<last>9942259</last>\n<when>1232755186</when>\n<utime>01/24/09 01:59 AM</utime>\n</post>"}